quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  4,135,"O you who have attained faith, always stand for justice, as witnesses for the sake of Allah, even if against yourselves or the parents or the close relatives. Whether a person is rich or poor, Allah is worthier as a patron of both. So do not follow prejudice{1}so as to do justice. <span class=""h"">But if you twist</span>(your testimony){2}or disregard<i class=""s"">(giving it) </i>—then indeed Allah has always been All-Aware of what you do.",footnotes:1:Literally, ‘whim’.,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Hamza read it as: “But whether you go forward (by testifying) or disregard…”</span>
  4,136,"O you who have attained faith, have faith in Allah and His Messenger and the Scripture which <span class=""h"">He</span><span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Ibn Amer read it as: “…and the Scripture which was bestowed upon…”</span>
  4,137,"Indeed, those who attained faith then denied, then attained faith then denied, then increased in denial—never is Allah to forgive them nor guide them to a way."
  4,138,"Give<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>glad tidings{1}to the hypocrites that they will have a painful punishment—",footnotes:1:This is said in sarcasm.
  4,139,"those who take the deniers as allies apart from the believers. Do they seek might from them? For indeed, all might belongs to Allah."
  4,140,"For<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Asem and Ya’qub read it as: “For it has surely been bestowed upon you….”</span>
